text: I was in college taking BS in Medical Technology but on my 3rd year I really feel like something's wrong and I shouldn't be there. I dropped out of my university last December 2021. For the whole year of 2022 I only worked on some side hustles online while trying to figure what I really want to do with my life. Then last September 2022 I saw "Data Analyst" in some online course ads. I started searching more about it in YT and found your channel. I really wanted to enroll to that online course but both tuition fee and new laptop costs a lot and we can't really afford it yet. In January 2023 I started watching your playlists in Excel, then SQL and lately I just finished the Power BI playlist. I also got a new laptop through installment plan. Right now I really just have to start working on projects for Excel, SQL and Power BI to have more hands-on experience. I actually decided to save learning Python for later since I'm currently preparing to apply for an entry-level Data Analyst position (they only require intermediate to advanced skill in Excel) but I might start learning Python soon after working on the projects you also posted here. Hopefully I get the position, earn some money and continue learning while working.  You're like a personal mentor to me Alex! I learned a lot from your channel. I still have a long way ahead. Wish me luck!
